  <h2>P-Median Problem with Demand Weights</h2>

  <h3>Sets and Parameters:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>I</strong>: Set of demand points</li>
    <li><strong>J</strong>: Set of candidate facility locations</li>
    <li><strong>d<sub>ij</sub></strong>: Distance or cost between demand point <em>i</em> and facility <em>j</em></li>
    <li><strong>w<sub>i</sub></strong>: Demand weight for demand point <em>i</em></li>
    <li><strong>P</strong>: Number of facilities to open</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Decision Variables:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>x<sub>ij</sub></strong>: 1 if demand point <em>i</em> is assigned to facility <em>j</em>, 0 otherwise</li>
    <li><strong>y<sub>j</sub></strong>: 1 if a facility is opened at location <em>j</em>, 0 otherwise</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Objective Function:</h3>
  <div class="math">
    \[
    \min \sum_{i \in I} \sum_{j \in J} w_i \cdot d_{ij} \cdot x_{ij}
    \]
  </div>

  <h3>Subject to:</h3>
  <div class="math">
    \[
    \sum_{j \in J} x_{ij} = 1 \quad \forall i \in I \quad \text{(Each demand point is assigned to one facility)}
    \]
    \[
    x_{ij} \le y_j \quad \forall i \in I, \forall j \in J \quad \text{(Assign only to open facilities)}
    \]
    \[
    \sum_{j \in J} y_j = P \quad \text{(Exactly } P \text{ facilities are opened)}
    \]
    \[
    x_{ij}, y_j \in \{0, 1\} \quad \forall i \in I, \forall j \in J \quad \text{(Binary decision variables)}
    \]
  </div>

